.TH FORG 1 "December 2025" "forg v1.0.0" "File Organizer Manual"
.SH NAME
forg \- Organize files into categorized subfolders
.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBforg\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBforg\fR is a command-line tool that organizes files in the current directory into categorized subfolders based on their file extensions. It provides automatic file categorization, recursive directory traversal, prefix support, and collision handling.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Directory Options
\fBforg\fR
.RS
Organize top-level files only (default behavior)
.RE
.PP
\fBforg\fR \fB\-r\fR
.RS
Recursive mode \- process all files in current directory and subdirectories
.RE
.PP
\fBforg\fR \fB\-r\fR \fB\-\-depth\fR \fIN\fR
.RS
Process files up to N levels deep (N >= 1)
.RE
.SS General Options
.PP
\fB\-r\fR, \fB\-\-recursive\fR
.RS
Enable recursive directory traversal
.RE
.PP
\fB\-d\fR, \fB\-\-depth\fR \fI<number>\fR
.RS
Maximum depth for recursion (default: 1)
.RE
.PP
\fB\-p\fR, \fB\-\-prefix\fR \fI<text>\fR
.RS
Add a prefix to category folder names (e.g., \fBbackup_Images\fR)
.RE
.PP
\fB\-v\fR, \fB\-\-verbose\fR
.RS
Show detailed progress information
.RE
.PP
\fB\-n\fR, \fB\-\-dry\-run\fR
.RS
Preview what would be done without making changes
.RE
.PP
\fB\-h\fR, \fB\-\-help\fR
.RS
Show this help message
.RE
.PP
\fB\-\-version\fR
.RS
Show version information
.RE
.SH CATEGORIES
\fBforg\fR organizes files into the following categories based on file extensions:
.PP
\fBImages\fR: jpg, jpeg, png, gif, bmp, tiff, svg, webp, ico, psd, ai, eps
.PP
\fBVideos\fR: mp4, mkv, avi, mov, wmv, flv, webm, m4v, mpeg, mpg, 3gp, rmvb
.PP
\fBAudio\fR: mp3, wav, flac, aac, ogg, m4a, wma, aiff, mid, midi
.PP
\fBDocuments\fR: pdf, doc, docx, txt, rtf, odt, xls, xlsx, ppt, pptx, csv, md, markdown, log
.PP
\fBArchives\fR: zip, rar, 7z, tar, gz, bz2, xz, iso, dmg, pkg, deb, rpm
.PP
\fBCode\fR: cpp, c, h, hpp, py, js, ts, html, htm, css, scss, java, go, rs, rb, php, swift, kt, scala, sh, bash, json, xml, yaml, yml, toml, ini, cfg, conf
.PP
\fBExecutables\fR: exe, app, bin, msi, run, elf, so, dll, dylib
.PP
\fBDatabase\fR: sql, db, sqlite, mdb, accdb, frm, ibd
.PP
\fBBooks\fR: epub, mobi, azw, azw3, fb2, djvu, chm
.PP
\fBOthers\fR: Files with unrecognized extensions
.SH SKIPPED ITEMS
The following files and directories are automatically skipped:
.PP
Hidden files (starting with '.')
.PP
Version control directories: .git, .svn, .hg, .bzr
.PP
IDE directories: .vscode, .idea, .vs
.PP
Build directories: build, dist, node_modules, .cache, __pycache__
.PP
System files: .DS_Store, Thumbs.db, .Spotlight-V100, .Trashes
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Organize top-level files in current directory:
.RS
\fBforg\fR
.RE
.PP
Organize all files recursively:
.RS
\fBforg\fR \fB\-r\fR
.RE
.PP
Organize files up to 2 levels deep:
.RS
\fBforg\fR \fB\-r\fR \fB\-\-depth\fR 2
.RE
.PP
Organize with prefix:
.RS
\fBforg\fR \fB\-p\fR backup_
.RE
.PP
Verbose mode with preview:
.RS
\fBforg\fR \fB\-v\fR \fB\-n\fR
.RE
